}, {\"ngram\": \"clips\", \"from\": 176, \"to\": 181}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PARIS \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 At the end of this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s opening ceremony, after the last athletes make their way down the Seine, disembark their boats and wait in line behind 11,000 other athletes for a scoop of Berthillon ice cream, somebody will have had the honor of lighting the Olympic cauldron.\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9979612459233901, \"rank\": 0.00204291908560891, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 226}, {\"ngram\": \"this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s opening ceremony\", \"from\": 230, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"the last athletes\", \"from\": 268, \"to\": 285}, {\"ngram\": \"their way\", \"from\": 291, \"to\": 300}, {\"ngram\": \"their boats\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 338}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 355}, {\"ngram\": \"11,000 other athletes\", \"from\": 363, \"to\": 384}, {\"ngram\": \"a scoop\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 396}, {\"ngram\": \"Berthillon ice cream\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 420}, {\"ngram\": \"somebody\", \"from\": 422, \"to\": 430}, {\"ngram\": \"the honor\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic cauldron\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It should be Zinedine Zidane.\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 502, \"end\": 517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Zidane, who led France to a 1998 World Cup triumph on home soil, is arguably the most important living and retired French athlete.\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 520, \"end\": 526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6791448805173827e-34, \"text\": \"Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}, {\"begin\": 536, \"end\": 542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8980867111348805, \"rank\": 0.11347822830207846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 635, \"end\": 641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9962434489530304, \"rank\": 0.003073251172187122, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 1998 World Cup triumph\", \"from\": 546, \"to\": 570}, {\"ngram\": \"home soil\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 583}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The child of Algerian immigrants, he grew up in La Castellane, a rough neighborhood in Marseille, and rose to the top of his sport.\", \"from\": 651, \"to\": 782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 664, \"end\": 672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algerian_War\", \"score\": 0.9970115858488197, \"rank\": 0.002997327220647229, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algerian_War\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algerian_War\"}, {\"begin\": 738, \"end\": 747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9983545132948477, \"rank\": 0.0016481987940129117, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"La Castellane\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 712}, {\"ngram\": \"a rough neighborhood\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 734}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 768}, {\"ngram\": \"his sport\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 781}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has identified himself as a non-practicing Muslim.\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.8555594982999155, \"rank\": 0.16882578241155252, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a fraught moment for France, as a party of anti-immigrant right-wing extremists\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094campaigning on a platform of racial intolerance\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094is coming dangerously close to assuming power.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 1023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 866, \"end\": 872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8980867111348805, \"rank\": 0.11347822830207846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a fraught moment\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"a party\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-immigrant right-wing\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 913}, {\"ngram\": \"extremists\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094campaigning\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 938}, {\"ngram\": \"a platform\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 952}, {\"ngram\": \"racial intolerance\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094is\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 979}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1022}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Giving Zidane the honor would make a clear statement about what it should mean to be French.\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Zidane\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"the honor\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"a clear statement\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zidane never played in theOlympics, so in a way, he would be an unconventional choice.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1118, \"end\": 1124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6791448805173827e-34, \"text\": \"Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theOlympics\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1152}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1165}, {\"ngram\": \"an unconventional choice\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is no rule that an Olympian has to light the cauldron.\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1234, \"end\": 1242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.408484717563322e-16, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no rule\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1225}, {\"ngram\": \"the cauldron\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the years, even non-athletes have kindled the flame.\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1327, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1284}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"the flame\", \"from\": 1317, \"to\": 1326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French could also lean hard into their national ethos and light the cauldron with a Gauloise.\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1425, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1332, \"end\": 1338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9962434489530304, \"rank\": 0.003073251172187122, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their national ethos\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"the cauldron\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1408}, {\"ngram\": \"a Gauloise\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1424}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the moment calls for a choice with political implications.\\u00c2 When Zidane became a star, far-right politician Jean-Marie Le Pen of the National Front bristled at the notion that Zidane and his multiethnic teammates really represented France.\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1496, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6791448805173827e-34, \"text\": \"Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}, {\"begin\": 1607, \"end\": 1613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6791448805173827e-34, \"text\": \"Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}, {\"begin\": 1663, \"end\": 1669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8980867111348805, \"rank\": 0.11347822830207846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1440}, {\"ngram\": \"a choice\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1459}, {\"ngram\": \"political implications\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1487}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"a star, far-right politician\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1537}, {\"ngram\": \"Jean-Marie Le Pen\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1555}, {\"ngram\": \"the National Front\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1577}, {\"ngram\": \"the notion\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1600}, {\"ngram\": \"his multiethnic teammates\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1642}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Le Pen also bristled at the notion that the Holocaust happened.\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1734, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1671, \"end\": 1677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"score\": 0.9999730248064617, \"rank\": 2.6975921217581183e-05, \"text\": \"Le Pen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the notion\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1705}, {\"ngram\": \"the Holocaust\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1724}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His daughter, Marine Le Pen, has rebranded the party as the National Rally and distanced herself from her father\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s beliefs.\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marine Le Pen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\"}, {\"begin\": 1795, \"end\": 1809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His daughter\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1747}, {\"ngram\": \"the party\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1787}, {\"ngram\": \"her father\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s beliefs\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1859}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But she has really just repurposed and redirected her father\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hate.\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 1931, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her father\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hate\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marine Le Pen wrote that she decried the barbarism of concentration camps \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cas early as 2011,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d as though voicing opposition to Nazi Germany in the year she turned 43 qualifies her for the Nobel peace prize.\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 2142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1933, \"end\": 1946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marine Le Pen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\"}, {\"begin\": 2063, \"end\": 2075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"score\": 0.9999745906297433, \"rank\": 2.3503291974102815e-05, \"text\": \"Nazi Germany\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the barbarism\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1983}, {\"ngram\": \"concentration camps\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2006}, {\"ngram\": \"opposition\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2059}, {\"ngram\": \"the year\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2087}, {\"ngram\": \"the Nobel peace prize\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2141}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has also called Muslim street prayers an \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009coccupation\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and said she wants to ban hijabs in public spaces.\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2163, \"end\": 2169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.8555594982999155, \"rank\": 0.16882578241155252, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009coccupation\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"hijabs\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2237}, {\"ngram\": \"public spaces\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2254}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(For this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Games, the French Sports Ministry hasbanned its athletes who observe the hijab from competingin the Paris Olympics, though they are permitted to wear hijabs in athletes\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 villages.)\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2286, \"end\": 2292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9962434489530304, \"rank\": 0.003073251172187122, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Games\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2280}, {\"ngram\": \"its athletes\", \"from\": 2319, \"to\": 2331}, {\"ngram\": \"the hijab\", \"from\": 2344, \"to\": 2353}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2389}, {\"ngram\": \"hijabs\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2431}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 villages\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2455}]}, {\"sentence\": \"National Rally president Jordan Bardella has said: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve experienced to the core the feeling of becoming a foreigner in one\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s own country.\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2459, \"end\": 2473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}, {\"begin\": 2484, \"end\": 2499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Bardella\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Bardella\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Bardella\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Bardella\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the core\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2543}, {\"ngram\": \"the feeling\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2555}, {\"ngram\": \"a foreigner\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"one\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s own country\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2602}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve experienced the Islamization of my neighborhood.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d I would like to believe that Bardella was misquoted, and that what he actually experienced was the llama-ization of his neighborhood; trust me when I tell you that as soon as you let the llamas in, traffic is a nightmare and public schools go to hell.\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2914, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Islamization\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2639}, {\"ngram\": \"my neighborhood.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 2662}, {\"ngram\": \"Bardella\", \"from\": 2692, \"to\": 2700}, {\"ngram\": \"the llama-ization\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2775}, {\"ngram\": \"his neighborhood\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2795}, {\"ngram\": \"the llamas\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2856}, {\"ngram\": \"traffic\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 2868}, {\"ngram\": \"a nightmare\", \"from\": 2872, \"to\": 2883}, {\"ngram\": \"public schools\", \"from\": 2888, \"to\": 2902}, {\"ngram\": \"hell\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 2913}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But no: Bardella was in fact complaining that people in his neighborhood did not share his religious beliefs, and this bothered him so much that he felt like a foreigner in his own country.\", \"fro